# Direct dependencies for the distillation training container.
# Transitive closure is resolved via ``pip-compile --generate-hashes``
# into ``requirements-distil.txt``; the Dockerfile installs the
# generated file with ``pip install --require-hashes`` so every
# resolved package is locked by SHA-256.
#
# ``optimum[onnxruntime]`` is deliberately NOT pinned here even
# though downstream export paths use it — the training script
# (``distil_v5_cloud.py``) is pure PyTorch, so baking ONNX tooling
# into the training image would only add attack surface without
# a runtime caller.
